  const GUIDE=`## Before sewing

- Choose one of the publisher's original sizes 00-32. A 1/2-inch seam allowance is included on sewn edges; place-on-fold edges have none.
- The open-back bodice is gathered and intentionally flexible. Make a test bodice and confirm the elasticized waist can pull over the body comfortably.
- Cut the base fabric first, then cut the overlay pieces. Transfer every notch, gather mark, fold line, and piece letter A-J.
- The skirt underlay and overlay use French seams. For the included 1/2-inch allowance, sew 1/4 inch wrong sides together, trim and press, then sew 1/4 inch right sides together.

## 1. Assemble the skirt (G and H)

Join center skirt panels G to the side panels H with French seams. Repeat for the overlay. Leave the marked pocket opening in each side seam.

## 2. Add pockets (J)

Match the pocket-opening notches and sew one pocket half J to each side-seam allowance. Place the pocket halves right sides together, sew around the bag, and reinforce where the pocket meets the side seam.

## 3. Close the back skirt

Join the back G panels at center back, keeping the overlay separate from the base layer. The pattern allows G to be cut on the fold or as a mirrored pair.

## 4. Prepare the gathered bodice (A and B)

Staystitch the overlay to front bodice B. Gather the shoulder and lower edges between the marked notches. Gather under-bodice A to the matching front-waistband marks, then align A and B at the sides.

## 5. Make the tabs and elasticized straps (C and D)

Fold shoulder tabs C right sides together, sew, turn, and press. Fold each strap D lengthwise and sew. Cut shoulder-to-waist elastic, thread it through D, and secure both ends so the elastic cannot retract.

## 6. Assemble the waistband (E and F)

Sew front waistband E to back waistband F at the side seams. Attach the gathered bodice to E. Join the skirt to the waistband, matching the waistband and skirt notches and side seams, and place the crossed straps at comfortable positions near the back side seams.

## 7. Finish the adaptive elastic back

Measure the wearer's back waist and cut elastic 1-2 inches shorter for comfortable stretch. Secure it at the side seams, fold F over the elastic, and stitch in stages while bunching the fabric. Slipstitch the folded edge of E over the front waist seam.

## 8. Make the detachable cape (I)

Gather or fan-fold the top of each shoulder drape I and enclose it in a shoulder tab C. Add buttonholes to the rear tabs and buttons to the shoulder tabs. Hooks and eyes, snaps, or hook-and-loop tape may be substituted for easier access.

## 9. Hem

Give the skirt a narrow rolled hem. Cut the overlay to the desired finished length and check the hem while wearing the intended shoes.`;

